name: Year of the Tiger
description:
Common Name: Amur Tiger
Latin Name: Panthera tigris altaica
Location: Russian Far East with a small number ranging across the border into northeastern China.
Conservation Status: Endangered

The Amur Tiger, sometimes also known as the Siberian Tiger, is the largest big cat in the world.

Photographed at Minnesota Zoo
FujiFilm FinePix S5100
August 31, 2005
